    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Japanese clay humanoid figures characteristic of the Jōmon period. These have stylized features such as large goggle-like eyes and exaggerated bodily proportions, though forms differed and evolved thoughout the period. Some are thought to be fertility symbols, but different forms may have had other functions.</Note_Text>
